#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also list only repositories with a particular name or show "
"information about a repository with a particular name and target. To list "
"repositories with a particular name, use the <command>smt-repos</command> "
"<replaceable>repository_name</replaceable> command. To show information "
"about a repository with a particular name and target, use the <command>smt-"
"repos</command> <replaceable>repository_name</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>target</replaceable> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get a list of installation repositories from remote, see <xref linkend="
"\"smt.clients.repolist\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selecting Repositories to Be Mirrored"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only enabled repositories can be mirrored. In the database, the enabled "
"repositories have the <literal>DOMIRROR</literal> flag set. Repositories can "
"be enabled or disabled using the <command>smt-repos</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid "To enable one or more repositories, follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to enable all repositories that can be mirrored or just choose "
"one repository from the list of all repositories, run the <command>smt-repos "
"-e</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can limit the list of repositories by using the relevant options. To "
"limit the list to only repositories that can be mirrored, use the <option>-"
"m</option> option: <command>smt-repos -m -e</command>. To limit the list to "
"only repositories with a particular name, use the <command>smt-repos -e</"
"command> <replaceable>repository_name</replaceable> command. To list only a "
"repository with a particular name and target, use the command <command>smt-"
"repos -e</command> <replaceable>repository_name</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>target</replaceable>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:214
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to enable all repositories belonging to a certain product, use "
"the <option>--enable-by-prod</option> or <option>-p</option> option followed "
"by the name of the product and, optionally, its version, architecture, and "
"release:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-repos -p <replaceable>product</replaceable>[,<replaceable>version</"
"replaceable>[,<replaceable>architecture</replaceable>[,<replaceable>release</"
"replaceable>]]]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, to enable all repositories belonging to &sls; 10 SP3 for "
"PowerPC architecture, use the <command>smt-repos -p SUSE-Linux-Enterprise-"
"Server-SP3,10,ppc</command> command. The list of known products can be "
"obtained with the <command>smt-list-products</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installer Self-Update Repository"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&smt; supports mirroring the installer self-update repository (find more "
"information in <xref linkend=\"sec.i.yast2.self_update.process\"/>). If you "
"need to provide the self-update repository, identify and enable it, for "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$ smt-repos -m | grep Installer\n"
"$ smt-repos -e SLES12-SP2-Installer-Updates sle-12-x86_64"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If more than one repository is listed, choose the one you want to enable by "
"specifying its ID listed in the repository table and pressing <keycap "
"function=\"enter\"></keycap>. If you want to enable all the listed "
"repositories, use <literal>a</literal> and press <keycap function=\"enter"
"\"></keycap>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:248
#, no-c-format
msgid "To disable one or more repositories, follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to disable all enabled repositories or just choose one "
"repository from the list of all repositories, run the <command>smt-repos -d</"
"command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to choose the repository to be disabled from a shorter list, or "
"if you want to disable all repositories from a limited group, you can use "
"any of the available options to limit the list of repositories. To limit the "
"list to only enabled repositories, use the <option>-o</option> option: "
"<command>smt-repos -o -d</command>. To limit the list to only repositories "
"with a particular name, use the <command>smt-repos -d</command> "
"<replaceable>repository_name</replaceable> command. To list only a "
"repository with a particular name and target, use the <command>smt-repos -d</"
"command> <replaceable>repository_name</replaceable> <replaceable>target</"
"replaceable> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If more than one repository is listed, choose which one you want to disable "
"by specifying its ID listed in the repository table shown and pressing "
"<keycap function=\"enter\"></keycap>. If you want to disable all the listed "
"repositories, use <literal>a</literal> and press <keycap function=\"enter"
"\"></keycap>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deleting Mirrored Repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can delete mirrored repositories that are no longer used. If you delete "
"a repository, it will be physically removed from the SMT storage area."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To delete a repository with a particular name, use the <command>smt-repos --"
"delete</command> command. To delete the repository in a namespace, specify "
"the <option>--namespace <replaceable>dirname</replaceable></option> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:297
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>--delete</option> lists all repositories, and by entering the ID "
"number or by entering the name and target you can delete the specified "
"repositories. If you want to delete all repositories, enter <guimenu>a</"
"guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:304
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detecting Repository IDs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Every repository has a sha1sum that you can use as an ID. You can get the "
"repository's sha1sum by calling <command>smt-repos -v</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mirroring Custom Repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using &smt; you can also mirror repositories that are not available at the "
"&scc;. Those repositories are called <quote>custom repositories</quote>. Use "
"the <command>smt-setup-custom-repos</command> command for this purpose. "
"Custom repositories can also be deleted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When adding a new custom repository, <command>smt-setup-custom-repos</"
"command> adds a new record in the database, and sets the <emphasis>mirror</"
"emphasis> flag to <replaceable>true</replaceable> by default. If needed, you "
"can disable mirroring later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set up a custom repository to be available through &smt;, follow these "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:333
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you do not know the ID of the product the new repositories should belong "
"to, use <command>smt-list-products</command> to get the ID. For the "
"description of the <command>smt-list-products</command>, see <xref linkend="
"\"smt.scripts.listproducts\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:341
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Run</para>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-setup-custom-repos --productid <replaceable>product_id</replaceable> \\\n"
"--name <replaceable>repository_name</replaceable> --exturl "
"<replaceable>repository_url</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this command <replaceable>product_id</replaceable> is the ID of the "
"product the repository belongs to, <replaceable>repository_name</"
"replaceable> represents the name of the repository and "
"<replaceable>repository_url</replaceable> is the URL the repository is "
"available at. In case the added repository needs to be available for more "
"than one product, specify the IDs of all products that should use the added "
"repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, to set <literal>My repository</literal> available at "
"<literal>http://example.com/My_repository</literal> to the products with the "
"IDs <literal>423</literal>, <literal>424</literal>, and <literal>425</"
"literal>, use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-setup-custom-repositories --productid 423 --productid 424 \\\n"
"--productid 425 --name 'My_repository' \\\n"
"--exturl 'http://example.com/My_repository'"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:364
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mirroring Unsigned Repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In its default configuration, &sle; 10 does not allow the use of unsigned "
"repositories. Therefore, if you want to mirror unsigned repositories and use "
"them on client machines, be aware that the package installation tool&mdash;"
"&yast; or <command>zypper</command>&mdash;will ask you whether to use "
"repositories that are not signed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:373
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove an already-set custom repository from the &smt; database, use "
"<command>smt-setup-custom-repositories --delete</command> <replaceable>ID</"
"replaceable>, where <replaceable>ID</replaceable> represents the ID of the "
"repository to be removed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:382
#, no-c-format
msgid "The /srv/www/htdocs Structure for SLE 11"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The path to the directory containing the mirror is set by the "
"<option>MirrorTo</option> option in the <filename>/etc/smt.conf</filename> "
"configuration file. For more information about <filename>/etc/smt.conf</"
"filename>, see <xref linkend=\"smt.config.smtconf\"/>. If the "
"<option>MirrorTo</option> option is not set to the Apache htdocs directory "
"<filename>/srv/www/htdocs/</filename>, the following links need to be "
"created. In case the directories already exist, they need to be removed "
"prior to creating the link (the data from those directories will be lost!):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/srv/www/htdocs/repo/$RCE</filename> should point to "
"<filename><replaceable>/MirrorTo</replaceable>/repo/$RCE/</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/srv/www/htdocs/repo/RPMMD</filename> to <filename><replaceable>/"
"MirrorTo</replaceable>/repo/RPMMD/</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/srv/www/htdocs/repo/testing</filename> to <filename><replaceable>/"
"MirrorTo</replaceable>/repo/testing/</filename> and"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/srv/www/htdocs/repo/full</filename> to <filename><replaceable>/"
"MirrorTo</replaceable>/repo/full/</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The directory specified by the option <option>MirrorTo</option> and the "
"subdirectories listed above must exist. Files, directories and links in "
"<replaceable>/MirrorTo</replaceable> need to belong to the user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">smt</systemitem> and the group <systemitem class="
"\"groupname\">www</systemitem>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, if the <option>MirrorTo</option> is set to <literal>/mirror/"
"data</literal>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"l /srv/www/htdocs/repo/\n"
"total 16\n"
"lrwxrwxrwx 1 smt  www    22 Feb  9 14:23 $RCE -&gt; /mirror/data/repo/$RCE/\n"
"drwxr-xr-x 4 smt  www  4096 Feb  9 14:23 ./\n"
"drwxr-xr-x 4 root root 4096 Feb  8 15:44 ../\n"
"lrwxrwxrwx 1 smt  www    23 Feb  9 14:23 RPMMD -&gt; /mirror/data/repo/"
"RPMMD/\n"
"lrwxrwxrwx 1 smt  www    22 Feb  9 14:23 full -&gt; /mirror/data/repo/full/\n"
"drwxr-xr-x 2 smt  www  4096 Feb  8 11:12 keys/\n"
"lrwxrwxrwx 1 smt  www    25 Feb  9 14:23 testing -&gt; /mirror/data/repo/"
"testing/\n"
"drwxr-xr-x 2 smt  www  4096 Feb  8 14:14 tools/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:442
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The links can be created using the <command>ln -s</command> commands. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"for LINK in \\$RCE RPMMD full testing; do\n"
"ln -s /mirror/data/repo/${LINK}/ &amp;&amp; chown -h smt.www ${LINK}\n"
"done"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:450
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <filename>/srv/www/htdocs/repo</filename> Directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>/srv/www/htdocs/repo</filename> directory must not be a "
