#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:493
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Test Environment"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can mirror repositories to a test environment instead of the production "
"environment. The test environment can be used with a limited number of "
"client machines before the tested repositories are moved to the production "
"environment. The test environment can be run on the main &smt; server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The testing environment uses the same structure as the production "
"environment, but it is located in the <filename>/srv/www/htdocs/repos/"
"testing/</filename> subdirectory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:508
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To mirror a repository to the testing environment, you can use the "
"<guimenu>Staging</guimenu> tab in the &yast; &smt; Management module, or the "
"command <command>smt-staging</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:514
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To register a client in the testing environment, modify <filename>/etc/"
"SUSEConnect</filename> on the client machine by setting:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:519 smt_mirroring.xml:714
#, no-c-format
msgid "namespace: testing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:521
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To move the testing environment to the production environment, manually copy "
"or move it using the <command>cp -a</command> or <command>mv</command> "
"command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:527
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can enable <quote>staging</quote> for a repository in the "
"<guimenu>Repositories</guimenu> tab of the &smt; Management module or with "
"the <command>smt-repos</command> command. The mirroring happens "
"automatically to <filename>repo/full/</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have an SLE11-based update repository with patches, &smt; tools can "
"help you with the management. With these tools you can select patches and "
"create a snapshot and copy it into <filename>repo/testing/</filename>. After "
"tests are finished you can copy the contents of <filename>repo/testing</"
"filename> into the production area <filename>/repo</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:543
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SLE10-based update repositories are not supported by &smt; tools. Not all of "
"these repositories support selective staging. In this case you must mirror "
"the complete package."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:549
#, no-c-format
msgid "Recommended work flow:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"repo =&gt; repo/full,\n"
"repo/full =&gt; repo/testing,\n"
"repo/testing =&gt; repo"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:557
#, no-c-format
msgid "Testing and Filtering Update Repositories with Staging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can test repositories on any clients with <command>smt-staging</command> "
"before moving them to the production environment. You can select new update "
"repositories manually to be installed on clients."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For staging, you can either use the <command>smt-staging</command> command, "
"or use the &yast; &smt; Management module. For more details, see <xref "
"linkend=\"smt.yast.staging.stage\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:572
#, no-c-format
msgid "&smt; Staging Schema"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:583
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Repositories with staging enabled are mirrored to the <filename>/"
"<replaceable>MirrorTo</replaceable>/repo/full</filename> subdirectory. This "
"subdirectory is usually not used by your clients. Incoming new updates are "
"not automatically visible to the clients before you get a chance to test "
"them. Later you can generate a testing environment of this repository, which "
"goes to <filename>/<replaceable>MirrorTo</replaceable>/repo</filename> "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:593
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have an SLE 11-based update repository with patches, &smt; tools can "
"help you with the management. With these tools you can select patches and "
"create a snapshot and put it into <filename>repo/testing/</filename>. After "
"tests are finished you can put the content of <filename>repo/testing</"
"filename> into the production area <filename>/repo</filename>. "
"<filename>repo/testing/</filename> and <filename>/repo</filename> is called "
"the <quote>default</quote> staging group. You can create additional staging "
"groups as needed with the <command>smt-staging creategroup</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:607
#, no-c-format
msgid "SLE 10-based Update Repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SLE 10-based update repositories are not supported by &smt; tools. Not all "
"of these repositories support selective staging. In this case you need to "
"mirror the complete package."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: smt_mirroring.xml:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling Staging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:619
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable or disable staging, use the <command>smt-repos</command> command "
"with <option>--enable-staging</option> or <option>-s</option>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "smt-repos --enable-staging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:624
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can enable the required repositories by entering the ID number or by "
"entering the name and target. If you want to enable all repositories enter "
"<guimenu>a</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: smt_mirroring.xml:632
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating Testing and Production Snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:634
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create the testing repository in the <quote>default</quote> staging group "
"enter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:638
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-staging createrepo <replaceable>Repository_ID</replaceable> -–testing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can test the installation and functionality of the patches in "
"testing clients. If no problems are discovered during testing, create the "
"production repository by entering:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:644
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-staging createrepo <replaceable>Repository_ID</replaceable> --production"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:645
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create testing and production repositories in a named staging group first "
"create the group and then the repositories in this group:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-staging creategroup <replaceable>Groupname</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>Testingdir</replaceable> <replaceable>Productiondir</"
"replaceable>\n"
"smt-staging createrepo --group <replaceable>Groupname</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>Repository_ID</replaceable> -–testing\n"
"smt-staging createrepo --group <replaceable>Groupname</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>Repository_ID</replaceable> -–production"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can help you if you, for example, want to combine SLES11-SP1-Updates "
"and SLES11-SP2-Updates of the <literal>sle-11-x86_64</literal> architecture "
"into one repository of a group:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:655
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-staging creategroup SLES11SP1-SP2-Up test-sp1-sp2 prod-sp1-sp2\n"
"smt-staging createrepo --group SLES11SP1-SP2-Up \\\n"
"  SLES11-SP1-Updates sle-11-x86_64 --testing\n"
"smt-staging createrepo --group SLES11SP1-SP2-Up \\\n"
"  SLES11-SP2-Updates sle-11-x86_64 --testing\n"
"smt-staging createrepo --group SLES11SP1-SP2-Up \\\n"
"  SLES11-SP1-Updates sle-11-x86_64 --production\n"
"smt-staging createrepo --group SLES11SP1-SP2-Up \\\n"
"  SLES11-SP2-Updates sle-11-x86_64 --production"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:656
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For group names, these characters are allowed: <literal>-_</literal>, "
"<literal>a-zA-Z</literal>, and <literal>0-9</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: smt_mirroring.xml:666
#, no-c-format
msgid "Filtering Patches"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can allow or forbid all or selected patches with the <command>allow</"
"command> or <command>forbid</command> commands by their ID or Category:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:673
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"smt-staging forbid --patch <replaceable>ID</replaceable>\n"
"smt-staging forbid --category <replaceable>Categoryname</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: smt_mirroring.xml:677
#, no-c-format
msgid "Signing Changed Repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:679
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you filter one or more patches from a repository, the original signature "
"becomes invalid. The repository needs to be signed again. The <command>smt-"
"staging createrepo</command> command takes care of that automatically if you "
"configure the &smt; server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable signing of changed metadata, the admin needs to generate a new "
"signing key. This can be done with GPG like this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:689
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mkdir <replaceable>some_dir</replaceable>\n"
"gpg --gen-key --homedir <replaceable>some_dir</replaceable>\n"
"sudo mv <replaceable>some_dir</replaceable> /var/lib/smt/.gnupg\n"
"sudo chown smt:users -R /var/lib/smt/.gnupg\n"
"sudo chmod go-rwx -R /var/lib/smt/.gnupg"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then the ID of the newly generated key, as seen in the <command>gpg --gen-"
"key</command> command output, must be written into <filename>/etc/smt.conf</"
"filename>, option <option>signingKeyID</option>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At this point the clients do not know about this new key. To import the new "
"key to clients during their registration, the following can be done:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:699
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sudo -u smt gpg --homedir /var/lib/smt/.gnupg \\\n"
"  --export -a <replaceable>signingKeyID</replaceable> \\\n"
"  &gt; /<replaceable>MirrorTo</replaceable>/repo/keys/smt-signing-key.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this example, <replaceable>MirrorTo</replaceable> stands for the base "
"directory where repositories will be mirrored. When done, clients can import "
"this key during the registration process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: smt_mirroring.xml:708
#, no-c-format
msgid "Registering Clients in the Testing Environment"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:710
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To register a client in the testing environment, modify the <filename>/etc/"
"SUSEConnect</filename> on the client machine by setting:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:720
#, no-c-format
msgid "Repository Preloading"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:722
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Although SUSE servers with software repositories are accelerated, deploying "
"multiple &smt; servers may become time consuming if each new &smt; server "
"must mirror the same repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:728
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To save time when deploying new &smt; servers, the repositories can be "
"preloaded from another server/disk instead. Follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:735
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable the repositories to be mirrored with the &smt;, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:738
#, no-c-format
msgid "smt-repos -e SLES12-Updates sle-12_x86_64"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:741
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Perform a dry run of <command>smt-mirror</command> to get the repository "
"directories created:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:745
#, no-c-format
msgid "smt-mirror -d --dryrun -L /var/log/smt/smt-mirror.log"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:746
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the repository above and the default <option>MirrorTo</option>, this "
"will create"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"/srv/www/htdocs/repo/repoindex.xml\n"
"/srv/www/htdocs/repo/$RCE/SLES12-Updates/sle-12-x86_64/*"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:753
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can copy over the repositories from another &smt; server, for "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:757
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"rsync -av 'smt12:/srv/www/htdocs/repo/\\$RCE/SLES12-Updates/sle-12-x86_64/' "
"\\\n"
" '/srv/www/htdocs/repo/$RCE/SLES12-Updates/sle-12-x86_64/'"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:760
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get the repository data fixed up, perform a normal <command>smt-mirror</"
"command>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: smt_mirroring.xml:764
#, no-c-format
msgid "smt-mirror -d -L /var/log/smt/smt-mirror.log"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: smt_mirroring.xml:769
#, no-c-format
msgid "Possible Error Messages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_mirroring.xml:770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Be prepared for errors such as <literal>repomd.xml is the same, but repo is "
"not valid. Start mirroring.</literal> These errors occur, since the metadata "
"about the preloaded repositories in the server's database is incorrect until "
"this initial mirror of the repositories has completed."
msgstr ""
